---
description: Performance guidance for static storefront + dashboard
---

## Storefront performance
- Prefer rendering with `DocumentFragment` for product lists (already used).
- Avoid re-querying DOM in loops; reuse `elements` references.
- Use cache wisely:
  - keep product cache TTL bounded (current 5 minutes)
  - handle storage quota failures gracefully
- Be careful with timers:
  - banner autoplay intervals must be cleared/reset correctly
  - avoid stacking intervals on repeated init

## Dashboard performance
- Prefer `cache: 'no-store'` only when necessary; otherwise use cache-busting intentionally (current uses `_t=` to force fresh).
- When polling (45s), skip updates while user is editing stock (already implemented).
- Avoid full re-render loops when a small state update suffices, unless simplicity is preferred.

## Network & API
- Keep payloads small; post only required fields.
- Maintain consistent response envelope; handle partial/missing fields defensively.
